<span id="freeTextContainer5402757780901690726">I can&apos;t imagine what it would have been like to have read this when it first was published. The power, the storm, the frenzy of Bellow&apos;s words is amazing. It is almost impossible to compare him to another writer. I don&apos;t mean to say that he is a better writer than others. It is just hard to group or contain him. He isn&apos;t bounded by boundaries. Sure, he is a madman, but there are no institutions built to contain him.</span>
