  <span id="freeText14767851224078954269" style="display:none">An authentic intellectual is always an outsider or even an outcast. <br />“He didn't feel that Poggioli had done full justice to certain important figures – Rozanov, for instance. Though Rozanov was cracked on certain questions, like the Jewish ritual bath, still he was a great figure, and his erotic mysticism was highly original – highly. Leave it to those Russians. What hadn't they done for Western Civilization, all the while repudiating the West and ridiculing it!”<br />So like a hermit crab one should find a shell and hiding in it live in the estrangement and alienation – an ultimate loner.</span>
